It allows you to be more compassionate, supportive, and respectful towards others, fostering positive relationships and a deeper sense of mutual understanding. How do you think empathy has influenced your own interactions with others?
transcript_llm: Empathy, huh? It's pretty fascinating how stepping into someone else's shoes can really change the game, you know. I feel like empathy has definitely shaped my interactions with others in a big way. When I take the time to understand where someone is coming from, it helps me communicate better and build trust with them. It's like a bridge that connects us on a deeper level, you know? And it makes me more mindful of how my words and actions can impact someone else's feelings. It's not always easy, but practicing empathy has definitely made me more patient and open-minded in my relationships.
